  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Preheat your grill to a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>to a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>(this softens the naturally hard cream)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion softens, rinse your <strong>red lentils </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>rinsed</strong> <strong>red lentils</strong> and <strong>green</strong> <strong>lentils</strong> (no need to drain)</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and <strong>softened</strong> <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> and cook for 15-20 min or until all the water is absorbed and the lentils are tender and porridge-like in consistency – this is your <strong>dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the dal is cooking, slice your<strong> flat white mushroom[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the<strong> mushroom wedges </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with the <strong>remaining sliced onion</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Place under the grill for 5-10 min or until nicely charred (keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn) – this is your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>mushroom & onion</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped ginger</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> until you're left with a smooth paste, then transfer the paste to a mixing bowl</p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the paste and mix to combine – this is your <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop everything very finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/592.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Taste the <strong>dal</strong> for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of boiled water if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Serve the <strong>dal</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>mushroom</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>onion </strong>– this is your<strong> crispy mushroom dal</strong></p><p>Dollop the <strong>coriander chutney</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
